# ===================================================================
# ðŸ“‹ USAGE NOTES
# ===================================================================
#
# ADMIN CAPABILITIES:
# âœ… Create users with any initial role
# âœ… Update ALL user fields (no restrictions)
# âœ… Soft delete users (recoverable)
# âœ… Hard delete users (permanent - admin only)
# âœ… Assign/remove roles from users
# âœ… View all users and filter by criteria
# âœ… Access user analytics and statistics
# âœ… System administration functions
# âœ… Override profile update restrictions
#
# CUSTOMER ADMIN CAPABILITIES:
# âœ… Manage users within their organization
# âœ… Assign roles (except admin)
# âœ… View user statistics
# âŒ Hard delete users
# âŒ System configuration changes
#
# ROLE HIERARCHY:
# admin > customer_admin > customer_support > base_user
#
# AVAILABLE ROLES:
# - admin: Full system access
# - customer_admin: Customer organization admin
# - customer_support: Customer support access  
# - base_user: Standard user access
#
# SECURITY FEATURES:
# - All endpoints require admin/customer_admin token
# - Hard delete restricted to admin role only
# - Role assignment follows business rules
# - All admin actions are audited and logged
# - Input validation on all operations
#
# TOKEN SETUP:
# 1. Run public.http â†’ "Admin Login"
# 2. Token automatically available as {{adminLogin.response.body.accessToken}}
# 3. Or set ADMIN_TOKEN environment variable
#
# ERROR HANDLING:
# - 401: Invalid or expired token
# - 403: Insufficient permissions (role hierarchy)
# - 400: Validation errors
# - 409: Conflict (duplicate email/username)
# - 422: Business rule violations
#
# BEST PRACTICES:
# - Use soft delete by default
# - Hard delete only for GDPR compliance
# - Regular audit of admin actions
# - Monitor role assignments
# - Implement approval workflows for sensitive operations 